The paper deals with the problem of embedding simplicial complexes in Euclidean space, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of complexity theory and NP-hardness results suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper also references algebraic topology and the theory of manifolds, which could place it in the sub-categories of geometric topology (cs.GT) and logic in computer science (cs.LO).
